# Azure Setup
Creating your VM is quite simple first search up Microsoft Azure and log into your account. 
Then Select Virtual machines.
Click create after that make sure you choose to Ubuntu Server 24.04LTS.
Then select the virtual size that is meant for your requirements.
After that is all done enable your SSH authentication.

# Connect to your SSH
Copy your ssh and put it somewhere safe it should look something like this.
ssh -i YourKeyName.pem User@YourwebserverIP
# Updating
Now open Powershell and update your system using these codes
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
